    <fr:title text="Universally closed map between topological spaces">Universally closed map between topological spaces</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  A continuous map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> between topological spaces is said to be <html:em>universally closed</html:em>, if the pullback of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> along any continous map is closed.
</html:p>
