          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  For a continuous map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> between topological spaces the following are equivalent:
  <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/topl-37K4/" title="Universally closed map between topological spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-37K4/" display-uri="topl-37K4" type="local">universally closed map between topological spaces</fr:link>. </html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is closed, and for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  Y]]></fr:tex> the inverse image <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(y)]]></fr:tex> is compact in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. </html:li></html:ol></html:p>
 
   
